<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="8">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Install the piston and connecting rod assemblies after the crankshaft has been properly
                    installed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn the crankshaft so the appropriate crankpin is at the bottom of its stroke.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the connecting rod bearing shells are properly installed in the bearing cap and
                the connecting rod.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200742" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1910.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Installing Protector Caps Onto the Connecting Rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Piston and Connecting Rod Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Protector Caps</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Bearing Shell (16)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install aluminum connecting rod protector caps onto the connecting rod bolt threads to help
                prevent damage to the crankshaft journals.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the cylinder bore, crankshaft journals, pistons, piston rings and the piston
                installation sleeve with clean engine oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before installing the piston into the ring compressor or the installation sleeve, make sure
                the ring gaps are oriented approximately 120&#176; apart.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, the arrow located on top of the piston must face the camshaft side of the
                    crankcase and the large chamfer on the connecting rod must be positioned next to the crankshaft
                    fillet.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200744" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Correct Orientation of a Properly Installed Piston</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Identification Marking</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200745" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1914.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Proper Position of an Installed Connecting Rod</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Pin Bushing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft Fillet</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bearing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Bearing (upper)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Bearing (lower)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Bearing Cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Large Chamfer Side (next to fillet)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Small Chamfer Side</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200746" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Piston and Connecting Rod Into the Cylinder Bore</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Bore</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Installation Sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the piston installation sleeve onto the piston. Make sure the rod bolts are seated.
                Carefully place the piston and connecting rod assembly into the crankcase bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200747" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1913.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Seating the Piston in the Cylinder Bore</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hammer Handle</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Installation Sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the handle of a hammer and tap the piston into the cylinder bore.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the connecting rod protector caps.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200748" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1917.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Connecting Rod and Cap Identification Marks</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Matching Connecting Rod and Cap Identification Marks</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure each connecting rod is matched with the its original bearing cap on the same
                crankpin from which they were removed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200749" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2591.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Lubricating and Installing the Connecting Rod Bearing Caps</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bearing Shell</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the bearing shell surfaces and connecting rod threads with clean engine oil. Install
                the bearing cap on the connecting rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not use any pneumatic tools when installing connecting rod nuts. This may cause the connecting
                    rod mounting nuts to seize.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200750" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1921.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Securing the Connecting Rod Cap</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Nuts (16)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod Bearing Cap (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connecting Rod (8)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten the connecting rod mounting nuts to the special torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the piston protrusion above the crankcase .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat the installation procedure for the remaining connecting rods and pistons.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
